{"title_page": "Rancocas Woods, New Jersey", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name            = Rancocas Woods, New Jersey\n|settlement_type = [[Local government in New Jersey#Unincorporated communities|Unincorporated community]]\n|nickname = \n|motto =\n\n<!-- Images -->\n|image_skyline = \n|imagesize = \n|image_caption = \n|image_flag = \n|image_seal =\n\n<!-- Maps -->\n|image_map = \n|mapsize = \n|map_caption = \n|image_map1 = \n|mapsize1 = \n|map_caption1 = \n|pushpin_map = USA New Jersey Burlington County#USA New Jersey#USA\n|pushpin_label = Rancocas Woods\n|pushpin_map_caption = Location in Burlington County (Inset: Burlington County in New Jersey)\n\n<!-- Location -->\n|subdivision_type = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name = {{flag|United States}}\n|subdivision_type1 = [[U.S. state|State]]\n|subdivision_name1 = {{flag|New Jersey}}\n|subdivision_type2 = [[List of counties in New Jersey|County]]\n|subdivision_name2 = [[Burlington County, New Jersey|Burlington]]\n|subdivision_type3 = [[Burlington County, New Jersey#Municipalities|Township]]\n|subdivision_name3 = [[Mount Laurel, New Jersey|Mount Laurel]]\n\n<!-- Government -->\n|government_footnotes = \n|government_type = \n|leader_title = \n|leader_name = \n|leader_title1 = \n|leader_name1 = \n|established_title = \n|established_date =\n\n<!-- Area -->\n|unit_pref  =  \n|area_footnotes = \n|area_magnitude = \n|area_total_km2 = \n|area_land_km2 = \n|area_water_km2 = \n|area_total_sq_mi = \n|area_land_sq_mi = \n|area_water_sq_mi =\n\n<!-- Population -->\n|population_as_of = \n|population_footnotes = \n|population_total = \n|population_density_km2 = \n|population_density_sq_mi =\n\n<!-- General information -->\n|timezone = [[Eastern Time Zone|Eastern (EST)]]\n|utc_offset = -5\n|timezone_DST = [[Eastern Daylight Time|Eastern (EDT)]]\n|utc_offset_DST = -4\n|elevation_footnotes = \n|elevation_m = \n|elevation_ft = 39\n|coordinates      = {{coord|39|59|20|N|74|51|37|W|region:US-NJ|display=inline,title}}\n\n<!-- Area/postal codes & others -->\n|postal_code_type = [[ZIP code]]\n|postal_code = 08054<ref>[http://tools.usps.com/go/ZipLookupResultsAction!input.action?resultMode=0&city=Rancocas%20Woods&state=NJ Look Up a ZIP Code for Rancocas Woods, NJ], [[United States Postal Service]]. Accessed June 18, 2013.</ref>\n|area_code = [[Area codes 609 and 640|609, 640]]\n|blank_name = [[Geographic Names Information System|GNIS]] feature ID\n|blank_info = 879610<ref>{{gnis|879610}}</ref>\n|blank1_name =\n|blank1_info = \n|website = \n|footnotes = \n}}\n'''Rancocas Woods''' is an [[Local government in New Jersey#Unincorporated communities|unincorporated community]] located within [[Mount Laurel, New Jersey|Mount Laurel Township]] in [[Burlington County, New Jersey|Burlington County]], [[New Jersey]], United States.<ref>[http://www.state.nj.us/infobank/localnames.txt Locality Search], State of [[New Jersey]]. Accessed June 9, 2016.</ref>\n\nThe community was developed on the site of an [[amusement park]]. Houses in Rancocas Woods were first built in the 1930s. There were problems with the community when first developed. No [[Sewerage|sewers]] were installed, because of limited [[drainage]], which caused floods to occur during heavy rainstorms.   The [[water pressure]] from [[fire hydrant]]s was unsubstantial\u2014the volunteer fire department had to pump its water from the nearby [[Rancocas Creek]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Our Town: Race, Housing, and the Soul of Suburbia|year=1997|publisher=[[Rutgers University Press]]|isbn=0-8135-2456-3|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FiHaUr7XjWgC&pg=PA48&dq=rancocas+woods+new+jersey&hl=en&ei=ZIEHTpf5HbOp0AHR5MnSCw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3&ved=0CDQQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=rancocas%20woods%20new%20jersey&f=false|author=David L. Kirp|author2=John P. Dwyer |author3=Larry A. Rosenthal |accessdate=June 26, 2011|page=48}}</ref>\n\n==Location==\nRancocas Woods is located on the Rancocas Creek, a major river that empties into the [[Delaware River]]. Exit 43 on [[Interstate 295 (Delaware \u2013 New Jersey)|Interstate 295]] can be used to access Rancocas Woods.  There is no direct exit on the [[New Jersey Turnpike]], however, the nearest exits to Rancocas Woods are exit 4 ([[New Jersey Route 73|Route 73]] \u2013 Mount Laurel) and exit 5 ([[County Route 541 (New Jersey)|County Route 541]] \u2013 [[Burlington, New Jersey|Burlington]], [[Mount Holly, New Jersey|Mount Holly]]).\n\n==Transportation==\n[[New Jersey Transit]] provides bus service to and from [[Philadelphia]] on the [[413 (New Jersey bus)|413]] route.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20100726183304/http://www.njtransit.com/sf/sf_servlet.srv?hdnPageAction=BusRoutesBurlingtonCountyTo Burlington County Bus / Rail Connections], [[New Jersey Transit]], backed up by the [[Internet Archive]] as of June 26, 2010. Accessed June 18, 2013.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Burlington County, New Jersey}}\n\n[[Category:Mount Laurel, New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Unincorporated communities in Burlington County, New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Unincorporated communities in New Jersey]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name            = Rancocas Woods, New Jersey\n|settlement_type = [[Local government in New Jersey#Unincorporated communities|Unincorporated community]]\n|nickname = \n|motto =\n\n<!-- Images -->\n|image_skyline = \n|imagesize = \n|image_caption = \n|image_flag = \n|image_seal =\n\n<!-- Maps -->\n|image_map = \n|mapsize = \n|map_caption = \n|image_map1 = \n|mapsize1 = \n|map_caption1 = \n|pushpin_map = USA New Jersey Burlington County#USA New Jersey#USA\n|pushpin_label = Rancocas Woods\n|pushpin_map_caption = Location in Burlington County (Inset: Burlington County in New Jersey)\n\n<!-- Location -->\n|subdivision_type = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name = {{flag|United States}}\n|subdivision_type1 = [[U.S. state|State]]\n|subdivision_name1 = {{flag|New Jersey}}\n|subdivision_type2 = [[List of counties in New J