rity|UK Civil Aviation Authority]]''<ref name=\"stats\"/></sup><br />\n{{reflist|group=\"nb\"}}\n|}\n\n===Busiest routes===\n<center>\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size: 87.5%\"\n|+ '''Busiest routes to and from Stansted (2018)<ref name=\"routestats\">{{cite web |url=http://www.caa.co.uk/Data-and-analysis/UK-aviation-market/Airports/Datasets/UK-Airport-data/Airport-data-2018/ |title=Airport Data 2018 |date=3 March 2019 |publisher=UK Civil Aviation Authority |at=Tables 12.1(XLS) and 12.2 (XLS) |access-date=5 March 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! Rank || Airport || Total <br>passengers || Change<br />2017 / 18\n|-\n|1|| {{flagicon|IRL}} [[Dublin Airport|Dublin]] ||align='right'| 898,295 || {{increase}} 0.8%\n|-\n|2|| {{flagicon|GBR}} [[Edinburgh Airport|Edinburgh]] ||align='right'| 732,022||{{increase}} 1.6%\n|-\n|3|| {{flagicon|GBR}} [[Belfast International Airport|Belfast\u2013International]] ||align='right'| 677,155||{{increase}} 80.2%\n|-\n|4|| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Ciampino\u2013G. B. Pastine International Airport|Rome\u2013Ciampino]] ||align='right'| 622,875||{{increase}} 1.0%\n|-\n|5|| {{flagicon|ESP}} [[M\u00e1laga Airport|M\u00e1laga]] ||align='right'| 541,450||{{increase}} 16.1%\n|-\n|6|| {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Barcelona El-Prat Airport|Barcelona]] ||align='right'| 480,917||{{increase}} 3.6%\n|-\n|7|| {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Palma de Mallorca Airport|Palma de Mallorca]] ||align='right'| 479,582||{{increase}} 6.9%\n|-\n|8|| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Orio al Serio International Airport|Bergamo]] ||align='right'| 476,531||{{increase}} 0.9%\n|-\n|9|| {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Adolfo Su\u00e1rez Madrid\u2013Barajas Airport|Madrid]] ||align='right'| 470,157||{{decrease}} 1.1%\n|-\n|10|| {{flagicon|DEU}} [[Berlin Sch\u00f6nefeld Airport|Berlin-Sch\u00f6nefeld]] ||align='right'| 453,167||{{increase}} 3.5%\n|-\n|11|| {{flagicon|DEU}} [[Cologne Bonn Airport|Cologne]] ||align='right'| 438,037||{{increase}} 5.6%\n|-\n|12|| {{flagicon|GBR}} [[Glasgow International Airport|Glasgow]] ||align='ri